=Show DHCP Relay Status=
This operation is used to view the DHCP Relay Status.

==Request==
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Method || GET
|-
|Request URI || 
* XML format
/vtns/{vtn_name}/vrouters/{vrt_name}/dhcprelay.xml
* JSON format
/vtns/{vtn_name}/vrouters/{vrt_name}/dhcprelay.json
|}

===Description of request URI elements===
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Element || Description || Required
|-
|vtn_name || VTN name.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters that can include
alphabets, numbers, and underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|-
|vrt_name || vRouter name.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters that can include
alphabets, numbers, and underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|}

===Request Body===
:None

==Response==
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Response Body ||
Response body
* XML format
 <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
 <dhcprelay dhcp_relay_status="{dhcp_relay_status}" />
* JSON format
 {
  "dhcprelay": {
        "dhcp_relay_status": "{dhcp_relay_status}"
   }
 }
|}

==Description of response elements===
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Element || Description
|-
|dhcp_relay_status || DHCP Relay status.
Valid value: enable, disable
|}

